o the nature of objects compiled in Scala 2.11. Execution may hinge on whether sun.reflect is initialized, particularly if the native image might have issues recognizing it. The question of how reachability metadata is generated for reflection methods seems crucial, especially when using targeted configuration. I'll need to consider how dynamically invoking methods affects this situation.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing reflection metadata needs**\\n\\nI'm considering whether the native image requires reflection metadata for the `sun.reflect.Reflection` public method if the class is part of the image. Since the user-code filter excludes certain paths, it might not generate necessary metadata for test helpers, potentially causing failures. It’s tricky since I don’t want to rely solely on the agent. I'm contemplating avoiding the helper entirely to sidestep metadata issues. Additionally, if the environment is using an older JVM version, there might be complications with called methods. I should touch on adding test files and configurations as well.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering testing actor creation**\\n\\nFor tests without arguments, I think creating `Props` to validate actor creation is important. We don’t necessarily need to involve the `ActorSystem` if `Props.actorClass` doesn’t yield results. It must use a public API rather than a private one. I’m pondering whether combining tests could lower the number of systems in use, but maybe keeping dedicated files is better. I need to be cautious about latches not counting actors, since construction happens before receiving messages, although counting during construction seems reasonable. However, the `Actor` constructor shouldn’t interact with the context.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring potential solutions**\\n\\nI'm considering whether I could use EventFilter. But wait, I don’t have access to a testkit right now. Maybe I should think about a global `ConcurrentLinkedQueue` as an alternative. This could help manage events more effectively. I'll need to weigh the pros and cons of each approach to determine the best path forward. There’s a lot to consider, especially without the testkit!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_uRmDLVFtKHXfjHOJwhFJYsHQ|fc_0733b0b1da64f9890169fb18f2868481958519232cc9bed0f5", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.typesafe.akka/akka-actor_2.13/2.8.8/src/test/scala/com_typesafe_akka/akka_actor_2_13/AkkaUtilReflectTest.scala", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage com_typesafe_akka.akka_actor_2_13\n\nimport java.util.concurrent.CountDownLatch\nimport java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit\nimport java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicReference\n\nimport akka.actor.Actor\nimport akka.actor.ActorSystem\nimport akka.actor.Props\nimport org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\n\nimport scala.concurrent.Await\nimport scala.concurrent.duration.DurationInt\n\nclass AkkaUtilReflectTest {\n  @Test\n  def createsActorWithPublicNoArgumentConstructor(): Unit = {\n    val latch: CountDownLatch = ReflectPublicNoArgsActor.expectCreation()\n\n    withActorSystem(\"reflect-public-no-args\") { system: ActorSystem =>\n      system.actorOf(Props(classOf[ReflectPublicNoArgsActor]), \"public-no-args\")\n      assertThat(latch.await(10, TimeUnit.SECONDS)).isTrue()\n    }\n  }\n\n  @Test\n  def createsActorWithPrivateNoArgumentConstructor(): Unit = {\n    val latch: CountDownLatch = ReflectPrivateNoArgsActor.expectCreation()\n\n    withActorSystem(\"reflect-private-no-args\") { system: ActorSystem =>\n      system.actorOf(Props(classOf[ReflectPrivateNoArgsActor]), \"private-no-args\")\n      assertThat(latch.await(10, TimeUnit.SECONDS)).isTrue()\n    }\n  }\n\n  @Test\n  def createsActorWithConstructorArguments(): Unit = {\n    val latch: CountDownLatch = new CountDownLatch(1)\n\n    withActorSystem(\"reflect-args\") { system: ActorSystem =>\n      system.actorOf(Props(classOf[ReflectArgsActor], \"constructed\", latch), \"args\")\n      assertThat(latch.await(10, TimeUnit.SECONDS)).isTrue()\n    }\n  }\n\n  @Test\n  def createsActorSystemWhenContextClassLoaderIsUnavailable(): Unit = {\n    val thread: Thread = Thread.currentThread()\n    val originalClassLoader: ClassLoader = thread.getContextClassLoader\n\n    thread.setContextClassLoader(null)\n    try {\n      withActorSystem(\"reflect-class-loader\") { system: ActorSystem =>\n        assertThat(system.name).isEqualTo(\"reflect-class-loader\")\n      }\n    } finally {\n      thread.setContextClassLoader(originalClassLoader)\n    }\n  }\n\n  private def withActorSystem(name: String)(body: ActorSystem => Unit): Unit = {\n    val system: ActorSystem = ActorSystem(name)\n    try {\n      body(system)\n    } finally {\n      Await.result(system.terminate(), 10.seconds)\n    }\n  }\n}\n\nclass ReflectPublicNoArgsActor extends Actor {\n  ReflectPublicNoArgsActor.markCreated()\n\n  override def receive: Receive = Actor.emptyBehavior\n}\n\nobject ReflectPublicNoArgsActor {\n  private val creationLatch: AtomicReference[CountDownLatch] = new AtomicReference[CountDownLatch]()\n\n  def expectCreation(): CountDownLatch = {\n    val latch: CountDownLatch = new CountDownLatch(1)\n    creationLatch.set(latch)\n    latch\n  }\n\n  def markCreated(): Unit = {\n    val latch: CountDownLatch = creationLatch.get()\n    if (latch != null) {\n      latch.countDown()\n    }\n  }\n}\n\nclass ReflectPrivateNoArgsActor private () extends Actor {\n  ReflectPrivateNoArgsActor.markCreated()\n\n  override def receive: Receive = Actor.emptyBehavior\n}\n\nobject ReflectPrivateNoArgsActor {\n  private val creationLatch: AtomicReference[CountDownLatch] = new AtomicReference[CountDownLatch]()\n\n  def expectCreation(): CountDownLatch = {\n    val latch: CountDownLatch = new CountDownLatch(1)\n    creationLatch.set(latch)\n    latch\n  }\n\n  def markCreated(): Unit = {\n    val latch: CountDownLatch = creationLatch.get()\n    if (latch != null) {\n      latch.countDown()\n    }\n  }\n}\n\nclass ReflectArgsActor(marker: String, latch: CountDownLatch) extends Actor {\n  if (marker == \"constructed\") {\n    latch.countDown()\n  }\n\n  override def receive: Receive = Actor.emptyBehavior\n}\n"}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"tests/src/com.typesafe.akka/akka-actor_2.13/2.8.8/src/test/scala/com_typesafe_akka/akka_actor_2_13/AkkaUtilReflectTest.scala\",\"content\":\"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage com_typesafe_akka.akka_actor_2_13\\n\\nimport java.util.concurrent.CountDownLatch\\nimport java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit\\nimport java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicReference\\n\\nimport akka.actor.Actor\\nimport akka.actor.ActorSystem\\nimport akka.actor.Props\\nimport org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\\n\\nimport scala.concurrent.Await\\nimport scala.concurrent.duration.DurationInt\\n\\nclass AkkaUtilReflectTest {\\n  @Test\\n  def createsActorWithPublicNoArgumentConstructor(): Unit = {\\n    val latch: CountDownLatch = ReflectPublicNoArgsActor.expectCreation()\\n\\n    withActorSystem(\\\"reflect-public-no-args\\\") { system: ActorSystem =>\\n      system.actorOf(Props(classOf[ReflectPublicNoArgsActor]), \\\"public-no-args\\\")\\n      assertThat(latch.await(10, TimeUnit.SECONDS)).isTrue()\\n    }\\n  }\\n\\n  @Test\\n  def createsActorWithPrivateNoArgumentConstructor(): Unit = {\\n    val latch: CountDownLatch = ReflectPrivateNoArgsActor.expectCreation()\\n\\n    withActorSystem(\\\"reflect-private-no-args\\\") { system: ActorSystem =>\\n      system.actorOf(Props(classOf[ReflectPrivateNoArgsActor]), \\\"private-no-args\\\")\\n      assertThat(latch.await(10, TimeUnit.SECONDS)).isTrue()\\n    }\\n  }\\n\\n  @Test\\n  def createsActorWithConstructorArguments(): Unit = {\\n    val latch: CountDownLatch = new CountDownLatch(1)\\n\\n    withActorSystem(\\\"reflect-args\\\") { system: ActorSystem =>\\n      system.actorOf(Props(classOf[ReflectArgsActor], \\\"constructed\\\", latch), \\\"args\\\")\\n      assertThat(latch.await(10, TimeUnit.SECONDS)).isTrue()\\n    }\\n  }\\n\\n  @Test\\n  def createsActorSystemWhenContextClassLoaderIsUnavailable(): Unit = {\\n    val thread: Thread = Thread.currentThread()\\n    val originalClassLoader: ClassLoader = thread.getContextClassLoader\\n\\n    thread.setContextClassLoader(null)\\n    try {\\n      withActorSystem(\\\"reflect-class-loader\\\") { system: ActorSystem =>\\n        assertThat(system.name).isEqualTo(\\\"reflect-class-loader\\\")\\n      }\\n    } finally {\\n      thread.setContextClassLoader(originalClassLoader)\\n    }\\n  }\\n\\n  private def withActorSystem(name: String)(body: ActorSystem => Unit): Unit = {\\n    val system: ActorSystem = ActorSystem(name)\\n    try {\\n      body(system)\\n    } finally {\\n      Await.result(system.terminate(), 10.seconds)\\n    }\\n  }\\n}\\n\\nclass ReflectPublicNoArgsActor extends Actor {\\n  ReflectPublicNoArgsActor.markCreated()\\n\\n  override def receive: Receive = Actor.emptyBehavior\\n}\\n\\nobject ReflectPublicNoArgsActor {\\n  private val creationLatch: AtomicReference[CountDownLatch] = new AtomicReference[CountDownLatch]()\\n\\n  def expectCreation(): CountDownLatch = {\\n    val latch: CountDownLatch = new CountDownLatch(1)\\n    creationLatch.set(latch)\\n    latch\\n  }\\n\\n  def markCreated(): Unit = {\\n    val latch: CountDownLatch = creationLatch.get()\\n    if (latch != null) {\\n      latch.countDown()\\n    }\\n  }\\n}\\n\\nclass ReflectPrivateNoArgsActor private () extends Actor {\\n  ReflectPrivateNoArgsActor.markCreated()\\n\\n  override def receive: Receive = Actor.emptyBehavior\\n}\\n\\nobject ReflectPrivateNoArgsActor {\\n  private val creationLatch: AtomicReference[CountDownLatch] = new AtomicReference[CountDownLatch]()\\n\\n  def expectCreation(): CountDownLatch = {\\n    val latch: CountDownLatch = new CountDownLatch(1)\\n    creationLatch.set(latch)\\n    latch\\n  }\\n\\n  def markCreated(): Unit = {\\n    val latch: CountDownLatch = creationLatch.get()\\n    if (latch != null) {\\n      latch.countDown()\\n    }\\n  }\\n}\\n\\nclass ReflectArgsActor(marker: String, latch: CountDownLatch) extends Actor {\\n  if (marker == \\\"constructed\\\") {\\n    latch.countDown()\\n  }\\n\\n  override def receive: Receive = Actor.emptyBehavior\\n}\\n\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 6573, "output": 3318, "cacheRead": 17920, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 27811, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778063568207, "responseId": "resp_0733b0b1da64f9890169fb18d0a8948195aef8df61ff273016"}}
[tool-exec] start id=call_uRmDLVFtKHXfjHOJwhFJYsHQ|fc_0733b0b1da64f9890169fb18f2868481958519232cc9bed0f5 name=write args={"path": "tests/src/com.typesafe.akka/akka-actor_2.13/2.8.8/src/test/scala/com_typesafe_akka/akka_actor_2_13/AkkaUtilReflectTest.scala", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage com_typesafe_akka.akka_actor_2_13\n\nimport java.util.concurrent.CountDownLatch\nimport java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit\nimport java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicReference\n\nimport akka.actor.Actor\nimport akka.actor.ActorSystem\nimport akka.actor.Props\nimport org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\n\nimport scala.concurrent.Await\nimport scala.concurrent.duration.DurationInt\n\nclass AkkaUtilReflectTest {\n  @Test\n  def createsActorWithPublicNoArgumentConstructor(): Unit = {\n    val latch: CountDownLatch = ReflectPublicNoArgsActor.expectCreation()\n\n    withActorSystem(\"reflect-public-no-args\") { system: ActorSystem =>\n      system.actorOf(Props(classOf[ReflectPublicNoArgsActor]), \"public-no-args\")\n      assertThat(latch.await(10, TimeUnit.SECONDS)).isTrue()\n    }\n  }\n\n  @Test\n  def createsActorWithPrivateNoArgumentConstructor(): Unit = {\n    val latch: CountDownLatch = ReflectPrivateNoArgsActor.expectCreation()\n\n    withActorSystem(\"reflect-private-no-args\") { system: ActorSystem =>\n      system.actorOf(Props(classOf[ReflectPrivateNoArgsActor]), \"private-no-args\")\n      assertThat(latch.await(10, TimeUnit.SECONDS)).isTrue()\n    }\n  }\n\n  @Test\n  def createsActorWithConstructorArguments(): Unit = {\n    val latch: CountDownLatch = new CountDownLatch(1)\n\n    withActorSystem(\"reflect-args\") { system: ActorSystem =>\n      system.actorOf(Props(classOf[ReflectArgsActor], \"constructed\", latch), \"args\")\n      assertThat(latch.await(10, TimeUnit.SECONDS)).isTrue()\n    }\n  }\n\n  @Test\n  def createsActorSystemWhenContextClassLoaderIsUnavailable(): Unit = {\n    val thread: Thread = Thread.currentThread()\n    val originalClassLoader: ClassLoader = thread.getContextClassLoader\n\n    thread.setContextClassLoader(null)\n    try {\n      withActorSystem(\"reflect-class-loader\") { system: ActorSystem =>\n        assertThat(system.name).isEqualTo(\"reflect-class-loader\")\n      }\n    } finally {\n      thread.setContextClassLoader(originalClassLoader)\n    }\n  }\n\n  private def withActorSystem(name: String)(body: ActorSystem => Unit): Unit = {\n    val system: ActorSystem = ActorSystem(name)\n    try {\n      body(system)\n    } finally {\n      Await.result(system.terminate(), 10.seconds)\n    }\n  }\n}\n\nclass ReflectPublicNoArgsActor extends Actor {\n  ReflectPublicNoArgsActor.markCreated()\n\n  override def receive: Receive = Actor.emptyBehavior\n}\n\nobject ReflectPublicNoArgsActor {\n  private val creationLatch: AtomicReference[CountDownLatch] = new AtomicReference[CountDownLatch]()\n\n  def expectCreation(): CountDownLatch = {\n    val latch: CountDownLatch = new CountDownLatch(1)\n    creationLatch.set(latch)\n    latch\n  }\n\n  def markCreated(): Unit = {\n    val latch: CountDownLatch = creationLatch.get()\n    if (latch != null) {\n      latch.countDown()\n    }\n  }\n}\n\nclass ReflectPrivateNoArgsActor private () extends Actor {\n  ReflectPrivateNoArgsActor.markCreated()\n\n  override def receive: Receive = Actor.emptyBehavior\n}\n\nobject ReflectPrivateNoArgsActor {\n  private val creationLatch: AtomicReference[CountDownLatch] = new AtomicReference[CountDownLatch]()\n\n  def expectCreation(): CountDownLatch = {\n    val latch: CountDownLatch = new CountDownLatch(1)\n    creationLatch.set(latch)\n    latch\n  }\n\n  def markCreated(): Unit = {\n    val latch: CountDownLatch = creationLatch.get()\n    if (latch != null) {\n      latch.countDown()\n    }\n  }\n}\n\nclass ReflectArgsActor(marker: String, latch: CountDownLatch) extends Actor {\n  if (marker == \"constructed\") {\n    latch.countDown()\n  }\n\n  override def receive: Receive = Actor.emptyBehavior\n}\n"}
