[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering class loading issues**\n\nI'm considering creating a binary class file under test resources, but there seems to be a classloader issue with the app. If I use a custom child-first loader, it could load the resource and define it, but I realize Gradle discovery might not scan these resources. I wonder if I should generate the bytes in code or use a Base64 literal instead. Also, I think I need a dedicated Scala test class to add a method for invoking the legacy caller class when loaded in an isolated class loader.\n\n**Exploring ClassLoader configurations**\n\nI'm constructing a custom child-first ClassLoader that overrides the loadClass method for \"akka.util.Reflect$\" and possibly all akka.* classes. I need to check if I can load Akka from the parent; if Reflect is loaded from the parent, then no. I plan to load Akka classes from the classpath using URLs from ProtectionDomain of ActorSystem/Reflect. It seems I have to manage dependencies carefully and ensure that child loading doesn't lead to conflicts when calling public APIs like akka.actor.ActorSystem.\n\n**Exploring dynamic class loading**\n\nI'm looking into dynamic class loading for Akka classes from an existing classpath in a native environment. It seems like ClassLoader.defineClass might not be supported, so I need to handle that case by catching the Error related to unsupported features. I'll verify it using NativeImageSupport from GraalVM. I’m curious if this dependency is included already or if I need to add the TCK plugin for testing support. Let's keep searching for clarity!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0733b0b1da64f9890169fb1a6fc3d0819581bf4ca03f668926\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-xqVrKb-6tGOG43UWgseuY6mQCVFd5fZvXJF8zAQ_uBezkoxJWbF_BljXkmpiEm4tF7jgPCpVsPB3syhaWJI5EplNCKr1it-DrNDIK4bjMW84aTXzdwEiHiOAHaTtDyl2LDQBtM2yKctnMWzt2icbl891Pa4MWKeJVNjKEkq-b